The paper discusses coreset construction algorithms for fundamental problems in machine/deep learning, computer vision, graphics, databases, and theoretical computer science. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.CG (computational geometry), cs.CV (computer vision), and cs.IT (information theory). Among these, cs.DS and cs.LG are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on the construction of accurate coresets for basic problems in machine learning and other fields, which are related to data structures and algorithms. However, the paper also discusses applications in computer vision and computational geometry, which could make cs.CV and cs.CG relevant categories as well. Finally, the paper includes some theoretical results and proofs, which could make cs.IT a possible category as well.
